<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>The State of Cancer — 20 Years of Global Data</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&family=Playfair+Display:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/d3/7.8.5/d3.min.js"></script>
<style>
*{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box}
:root{
  --bg:#FAF8F4;--card:#F3EBE0;--cardHover:#EDE4D6;
  --text:#2F2A26;--muted:#7A746C;--light:#A89B8C;
  --teal:#2A7B6F;--tealBg:rgba(42,123,111,0.10);
  --rust:#B5634B;--rustBg:rgba(181,99,75,0.10);
  --blue:#3A5A7C;--copper:#A0764D;--gold:#B08845;--navy:#2C3E50;
  --grid:#E6DED3;--axis:#CFC7BB;
}
html{scroll-behavior:smooth}
body{background:var(--bg);color:var(--text);font-family:'Inter','Helvetica Neue',sans-serif;font-weight:400;line-height:1.6;overflow-x:hidden}

/* NAV */
nav{position:fixed;top:0;left:0;right:0;z-index:100;background:rgba(250,248,244,0.92);backdrop-filter:blur(12px);border-bottom:1px solid rgba(47,42,38,0.06);padding:0 2rem;display:flex;align-items:center;height:50px;gap:2rem}
nav .logo{font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:14px;font-weight:700;white-space:nowrap;color:var(--text)}
nav .nav-links{display:flex;gap:4px;overflow-x:auto;scrollbar-width:none}
nav .nav-links::-webkit-scrollbar{display:none}
nav a{font-size:10.5px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.06em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);text-decoration:none;padding:6px 10px;border-radius:6px;white-space:nowrap;transition:all 0.2s}
nav a:hover,nav a.active{color:var(--text);background:rgba(47,42,38,0.05)}

/* PROGRESS */
.progress-bar{position:fixed;top:50px;left:0;height:2px;background:var(--copper);z-index:101;width:0%;transition:width 0.1s}

/* SECTIONS */
.section{padding:4.5rem 2rem 3.5rem;max-width:1020px;margin:0 auto;opacity:0;transform:translateY(30px);transition:opacity 0.7s ease,transform 0.7s ease}
.section.visible{opacity:1;transform:translateY(0)}

.section-eyebrow{font-size:9.5px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:0.10em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:6px}
.section-title{font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:24px;font-weight:700;line-height:1.15;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:6px}
.section-subtitle{font-size:13px;line-height:1.5;color:var(--muted);max-width:680px;margin-bottom:16px}

/* HERO */
#hero{text-align:center;padding-top:8rem;padding-bottom:3rem}
#hero .section-title{font-size:clamp(24px,4.5vw,36px);max-width:720px;margin:0 auto 10px}
#hero .section-subtitle{max-width:580px;margin:0 auto 24px}

/* KPI GRID */
.kpi-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:12px;margin:14px 0 18px}
.kpi-card{background:var(--card);border-radius:12px;padding:14px 14px 12px}
.kpi-label{font-size:9px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:6px}
.kpi-value{font-size:24px;font-weight:700;line-height:1;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:6px}
.kpi-note{font-size:12px;line-height:1.4;color:var(--muted)}

/* CHART WRAP */
.chart-wrap{overflow-x:auto;-webkit-overflow-scrolling:touch;margin:8px 0}
.chart-wrap svg{display:block}

/* CONTEXT STRIP */
.context-strip{display:flex;gap:16px;margin:0 auto;max-width:1020px;padding:0 2rem 2rem;align-items:center}
.ctx-img{width:140px;height:90px;border-radius:10px;object-fit:cover;flex-shrink:0;background:var(--card)}
.ctx-text{font-size:13px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.55}
.ctx-text strong{color:var(--text);font-weight:600}
.ctx-card{background:var(--card);border-radius:12px;padding:16px 18px}

/* CAPTION */
.chart-caption{font-size:12px;line-height:1.5;color:var(--muted);margin:8px 0 0}

/* SPARKLINE GRID */
.spark-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:12px;max-width:980px}
.spark-cell{background:var(--card);border-radius:12px;padding:14px 14px 12px;border:1.5px solid transparent;cursor:pointer;transition:all 0.2s}
.spark-cell:hover{background:var(--cardHover)}
.spark-cell.active{background:var(--cardHover);border-color:var(--copper)}
.spark-header{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:flex-start;gap:12px;margin-bottom:4px}
.spark-name{font-size:15px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text)}
.spark-badge{font-size:11px;font-weight:700;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:999px;color:#fff}
.spark-note{font-size:11.5px;line-height:1.4;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:8px}

/* EXPAND PANEL */
.expand-panel{max-width:980px;background:var(--card);border:1.5px solid var(--copper);border-radius:12px;padding:16px;margin-top:12px;animation:slideDown 0.35s ease}
@keyframes slideDown{from{opacity:0;transform:translateY(-8px)}to{opacity:1;transform:translateY(0)}}
.expand-title{font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:4px}
.expand-note{font-size:12px;line-height:1.5;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:12px}

/* SEX TOGGLE */
.sex-toggle{display:inline-flex;gap:0;border:1.5px solid var(--grid);border-radius:8px;overflow:hidden;margin-bottom:12px}
.sex-toggle button{font-family:inherit;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;padding:6px 18px;border:none;background:transparent;color:var(--muted);cursor:pointer;transition:all 0.15s}
.sex-toggle button.active{background:var(--card);color:var(--text)}

/* TAKEAWAY */
.takeaway-card{background:var(--card);border-radius:12px;padding:18px 20px;max-width:980px;margin:0 auto}
.takeaway-eyebrow{font-size:12px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:8px}
.takeaway-headline{font-size:18px;font-weight:700;line-height:1.35;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:8px}
.takeaway-body{font-size:13px;line-height:1.65;color:var(--muted)}

/* FOOTER */
footer{text-align:center;padding:2rem;font-size:11px;color:var(--light)}

@media(max-width:700px){
  .kpi-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr}
  .spark-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}
  .section{padding:3.5rem 1.25rem 2.5rem}
  .context-strip{flex-direction:column;padding:0 1.25rem 2rem}
  .ctx-img{width:100%;height:120px}
  nav{padding:0 1rem}
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="progress-bar" id="progressBar"></div>

<nav>
  <div class="logo">The State of Cancer</div>
  <div class="nav-links">
    <a href="#hero">Overview</a>
    <a href="#mortality">Mortality</a>
    <a href="#compare">CAN vs AUS</a>
    <a href="#sparklines">Landscape</a>
    <a href="#heatmap">Incidence</a>
    <a href="#funding">Funding</a>
    <a href="#direction">Pathways</a>
  </div>
</nav>

<!-- HERO -->
<div id="hero" class="section">
  <div class="section-eyebrow">CPSC 582 · Cancer Dashboard</div>
  <div class="section-title">Cancer outcomes improved unevenly — across countries, across cancers, and across time.</div>
  <p class="section-subtitle">This dashboard uses colorectal cancer as the main comparison case, then broadens to Canadian cancer trends and funding gaps. Progress depends on when screening starts, how treatment evolves, and whether research investment matches burden.</p>
  <div class="kpi-grid" id="kpiGrid"></div>
</div>

<!-- VIZ 1 -->
<div id="mortality" class="section">
  <div class="section-eyebrow">Visualization 01</div>
  <div class="section-title">Colorectal Cancer Mortality — Who Improved and Who Worsened</div>
  <p class="section-subtitle">Percentage change in age-standardized mortality rate, 1997 to 2017. The top three and bottom three countries tell starkly different stories.</p>
  <div class="chart-wrap" id="viz1"></div>
</div>

<!-- CONTEXT -->
<div class="context-strip">
  <div class="ctx-card" style="display:flex;gap:16px;align-items:center;width:100%">
    <img class="ctx-img" src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1579684385127-1ef15d508118?w=300&h=200&fit=crop" alt="Medical" onerror="this.style.display='none'">
    <div class="ctx-text"><strong>Why such stark differences?</strong> Countries that invested early in organized screening (Czechia 2000, Australia 2006) and adopted FOLFOX (2000) and bevacizumab (2004) saw dramatic drops. Countries without screening infrastructure saw mortality double.</div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- VIZ 2 -->
<div id="compare" class="section">
  <div class="section-eyebrow">Visualization 02</div>
  <div class="section-title">The Screening Divide — Canada vs Australia</div>
  <p class="section-subtitle">Both started with similar CRC burdens. Australia's mortality dropped twice as fast. Gold dashed lines mark FOLFOX (2000), bevacizumab (2004), Australia NBCSP (2006), and Ontario ColonCancerCheck (2008).</p>
  <div class="sex-toggle" id="sexToggle">
    <button class="active" data-sex="M">Male</button>
    <button data-sex="F">Female</button>
  </div>
  <div class="chart-wrap" id="viz2"></div>
  <p class="chart-caption" id="viz2caption"></p>
</div>

<!-- VIZ 3 -->
<div id="sparklines" class="section">
  <div class="section-eyebrow">Visualization 03</div>
  <div class="section-title">Where Canada Has Made Progress — and Where It Hasn't</div>
  <p class="section-subtitle">Click any card to see incidence alongside mortality, plus contextual factors. The gap between the lines is the survival story.</p>
  <div class="spark-grid" id="sparkGrid"></div>
  <div id="sparkDetail"></div>
</div>

<!-- CONTEXT -->
<div class="context-strip">
  <div class="ctx-card" style="display:flex;gap:16px;align-items:center;width:100%">
    <img class="ctx-img" src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1532187863486-abf9dbad1b69?w=300&h=200&fit=crop" alt="Lab" onerror="this.style.display='none'">
    <div class="ctx-text"><strong>Pancreas and brain cancers haven't budged.</strong> Pancreatic cancer 5-year survival moved from ~6% to ~12% in 20 years — still the lowest of any major cancer. Brain cancer's best drug (temozolomide, 2005) added only 2.5 months. No improvement since.</div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- VIZ 4 -->
<div id="heatmap" class="section">
  <div class="section-eyebrow">Visualization 04</div>
  <div class="section-title">Global CRC Incidence — Largest Declines vs Largest Increases</div>
  <p class="section-subtitle">Each row is a country's incidence trajectory normalized to its 1997 baseline. Teal = fewer diagnoses, copper = more.</p>
  <div class="chart-wrap" id="viz4"></div>
</div>

<!-- VIZ 5 -->
<div id="funding" class="section">
  <div class="section-eyebrow">Visualization 05</div>
  <div class="section-title">Cancer Burden vs Research Investment</div>
  <p class="section-subtitle">Selected cancers where death share exceeds investment share. Lung cancer accounts for 24% of deaths but receives just 7% of research funding.</p>
  <div class="chart-wrap" id="viz5"></div>
  <p class="chart-caption">These selected cancers appear underfunded relative to mortality burden, with lung showing the largest mismatch.</p>
</div>

<!-- VIZ 6 -->
<div id="direction" class="section">
  <div class="section-eyebrow">Visualization 06</div>
  <div class="section-title">Same Destination, Different Paths</div>
  <p class="section-subtitle">How did incidence and mortality move together — or apart? Countries where both fell achieved prevention. Where only mortality fell, treatment is winning but cases are still rising.</p>
  <div class="chart-wrap" id="viz6"></div>
  <p class="chart-caption">Countries sorted by mortality change. Gold dots mark those with organized screening programs. The clustering is immediate — screening countries improved on both measures.</p>
</div>

<!-- TAKEAWAY -->
<div class="section visible">
  <div class="takeaway-card">
    <div class="takeaway-eyebrow">Final takeaway</div>
    <div class="takeaway-headline">Cancer progress is uneven: screening, treatment breakthroughs, and research attention do not arrive equally across cancers or countries.</div>
    <div class="takeaway-body">Colorectal cancer shows that outcomes can improve substantially, but the pace depends on when screening starts and how treatment evolves. Across Canada more broadly, some cancers improved sharply, while others remained stubborn or worsened. Research investment also does not consistently track burden, leaving some high-mortality cancers with relatively limited support.</div>
  </div>
</div>

<footer>
  Data: IARC Global Cancer Observatory (Cancer Over Time) · Canadian Cancer Research Alliance · CCRA Supplementary Data 2022<br>
  World Bank · NCD-RisC · CONCORD-3 · Health Canada · PHAC<br>
